  "text": "where the potentials V and K satisfy rather generic conditions, allowing V even to vanish on the infinity. To do so they use a modification of the penalization technique, originally presented in [CITATION_1] , in such a way that compactness is recovered to the modified energy functional. Because of the generality of conditions under with V and K are subjected, in order to prove that the solutions of the modified problem are solutions of the original one, they made a thorough analysis with some barrier functions which bounds the solutions from above. In [CITATION_2] the authors employ a similar argument in order to show the existence of solutions concentrating on circumferences of R 3 , to a Schrödinger-Poisson system.",
